thread.title: Ranji Trophy: Chahar, Choudhary send Delhi packing
thread.title_full: Ranji Trophy: Chahar, Choudhary send Delhi packing - The Times of India

author: Ashish Sen
title: Ranji Trophy: Chahar, Choudhary send Delhi packing
text:
JAIPUR: Seam bowler Deepak Chahar returned to action with a five-wicket haul as he lead a disciplined Team Rajasthan attack to dismiss Delhi for a paltry 138 in the first innings on the opening day of the Ranji Trophy Group A match at Sawai Mansingh Stadium here on Thursday. With good pace and bounce on the wicket, Aniket Choudhary turned out to be other tormentor, picking up three wickets. The hosts ended the day at 743.
Besides Chahar (560) and Aniket (326), 20-year old Nathu Singh, who celebrated his debut by snapping up a wicket, impressed with his medium pace. Gambhir's boys could have been bowled out before the lunch break, had the enthusiastic debutant not bowled two no-balls.
Shifting to Sikar from Jaipur proved a blessing as Nathu's subsequent performances helped him earn a zonal call, which eventually led to a stint at the National Cricket Academy in Bangalore last year.
On Thursday, a number of the supporters travelled all the way from Sikar to cheer him.
